I'll help you implement infinite scrolling in your Shopify store. Here's a clear step-by-step guide:

1. First, locate your collection template file:

```liquid:sections/collection-template.liquid
{% paginate collection.products by 12 %}
  <div id="product-grid" data-collection>
    {% for product in collection.products %}
      {% render 'product-card', product: product %}
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
{% endpaginate %}
```

2. Add jQuery to your theme if not already present:

```liquid:layout/theme.liquid
{{ 'jquery-3.6.0.min.js' | asset_url | script_tag }}
```

3. Create a new JavaScript file for infinite scroll:

```javascript:assets/infinite-scroll.js
$(document).ready(function() {
  let currentPage = 1;
  let loading = false;

  $(window).scroll(function() {
    if($(window).scrollTop() + $(window).height() >= $(document).height() - 100) {
      if(!loading) {
        loading = true;
        currentPage++;

        $.ajax({
          url: window.location.href,
          type: 'GET',
          data: { page: currentPage },
          success: function(data) {
            let $newProducts = $(data).find('#product-grid [data-product-card]');
            if($newProducts.length > 0) {
              $('#product-grid').append($newProducts);
              loading = false;
            }
          }
        });
      }
    }
  });
});
```

4. Add a loading indicator to your collection template:

```liquid:sections/collection-template.liquid
<div id="loading-spinner" style="display: none;">
  <span class="loading-text">Loading more products...</span>
</div>
```

5. Add CSS for the loading indicator:

```css:assets/custom.css
#loading-spinner {
  text-align: center;
  padding: 20px;
  margin: 20px 0;
}

.loading-text {
  display: inline-block;
  font-size: 16px;
  color: #666;
}
```

6. Include the new JavaScript file in your theme:

```liquid:layout/theme.liquid
{{ 'infinite-scroll.js' | asset_url | script_tag }}
```

